The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 October is 3,759 (435.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 October, there were 231 new confirmed cases (26.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 September, there were 159 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 45% (72 extra cases).
